subSubSection.paragraph:
Receptacle consisting of a lower uniseriate row of 4–25 cells derived from cell II. Cell III irregularly divided into several small cells. Primary septum constricted and darkened. Primary appendage irregular, consisting of some embedded antheridia giving rise to short efferent necks, and a variable number of cells, some of them giving rise to sterile branches. [Detailed descriptions: 
Thaxter 1931
; 
Sugiyama 1973
; 
Santamaria 1989
; 
Majewski 1994b
]

